# D365 F&O Extensible Design

Microsoft source: [Write extensible code](https://learn.microsoft.com/dynamics365/fin-ops-core/dev-itpro/extensibility/writing-extensible-code)

## Core rules

- Methods **5–10 lines**, ≤2 parameters
- Minimize surface: `private` > `internal` > `protected` > `public`
- **DRY** — no duplicated logic across extension points
- Extract switch defaults to `[Replaceable]` methods
- Use `parm*` accessors; params prefixed with `_`

## Scenarios and recommendations

### New application service class

**Recommend:** Single responsibility; public methods delegate to small protected methods; inject behavior via CoC on protected methods where extenders need hooks.

**Avoid:** 200-line `run()`; public fields; calling kernel/system classes directly.

### Extending standard process without copying method

**Recommend:** CoC on extracted sub-methods; `[Replaceable]` for switch defaults.

**Avoid:** Copy entire standard method into extension class.

### Duplicate logic in CoC + event handler

**Recommend:** One private method on extension class; both entry points call it.

**Avoid:** Same validation copied in form CoC and table CoC with drift risk.

### Batch / SysOperation service structure

**Recommend:** Controller → service → contract; service methods ≤10 lines; `parm*` for state.

**Avoid:** Business logic in controller; many boolean params — use contract class.

### Factory / plug-in specialization

**Recommend:** Depend on interface or base class; Liskov-safe implementations registered via SysExtension.

**Avoid:** `switch` on company or module enum for implementation choice in consumer.

## Extract example

```xpp
// BAD — blocking default prevents extension
public void processOrder(SalesId _salesId)
{
    switch (orderType)
    {
        case TypeA: /* ... */
        case TypeB: /* ... */
        default: throw error("@SYS21468");
    }
}

// GOOD
public void processOrder(SalesId _salesId)
{
    this.validateOrder(_salesId);
    this.processOrderByType(_salesId); // Replaceable / CoC target
}
```

